item.title: Ip 0.0.0.0?not correct
item.dc:creator: @Owner_Spyder Owner Spyder
item.description:
@Owner_Spyder wrote:

Your ip is not 0.0.0.0, thats your ip to log onto your server when you run it. People will log on your server with the ip you choose either from no-ip or some some place else.

item.title: Ip 0.0.0.0?not correct
item.dc:creator: @ziplock ziplock
item.description:
@ziplock wrote:

[quote=“sinzscape, post:1, topic:268287”]mopar, man help me out. I have a source already but my ip is 0.0.0.0, how do i fix it to my ip??

please help mopar!@!@!! :D[/quote]

You do not “fix” your ip. You need to portforward your router (If you have one) to open the port that your server operates off of. www.Portforward.com (Check your router model.)
